    "body": "This is what happens when you only use a code fence, no language specified. There are no `<span>` tags inside the code block, and this renders OK in the slides:\n\n```\n<pre><code>mkdir my-new-machine\nvagrant init http://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/vagrant/trusty/current/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-vagrant-disk1.box\nvagrant up\n</code></pre>\n```\n\nThis is what happens when I specify language `shell` for the fenced code block. Now there are span tags and they are shown in the rendered version (which is sort of expected for `<pre>`, although in the ipython notebook itself, these are not shown):\n\n```\n<pre><code class=\"language-shell\">mkdir my-new-machine\nvagrant init http://cloud-images<span class=\"preprocessor\">.ubuntu</span><span class=\"preprocessor\">.com</span>/vagrant/trusty/current/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-vagrant-disk1<span class=\"preprocessor\">.box</span>\nvagrant up\n</code></pre>\n```\n\nI've had a quick look at zenburn.css but have not yet been able to figure out how to fix this problem.\n"
